SIMPLE: unlade
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unlade
<hw>Un*lade"</hw> <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st <ets>un-</ets> +
<ets>lade</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To take the load from; to take
out the cargo of; <as>as, to <ex>unlade</ex> a ship or a
wagon</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The venturous merchant . . . ⟦br⟧
Shall here <qex>unlade</qex> him and depart no more.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To unload; to remove, or to have removed, as a load
or a burden; to discharge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There the ship was to <qex>unlade</qex> her burden.</q>
<rj><qau>Acts. xxi. 3.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unlaid</ent>⟦br⟧
